The paper deals with information-theoretic aspects of secret key agreement, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It also involves cryptography (cs.CR) since the goal is to agree on a secret key that is independent of an eavesdropper's observation. The interactive communication aspect suggests that it may be related to communication complexity (cs.CC). The paper also mentions the possibility of applying the results to non-i.i.d. or non-ergodic sources, which could be related to data structures (cs.DS) or signal processing (cs.SI).
